disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Absolution.

blurb.value: Senna's Relic Cannon is slow to fire, but deals bonus damage. She can power up its range, Attack Damage, and Crit chance over time by absorbing Mist from enemy champions she's attacking or from wraiths that spawn from dead enemies.

description.value: Innate - Weakened Soul: Senna's basic attacks on-hit and damaging abilities on enemy champions apply Mist for 4 seconds, refreshed to 0.75 seconds if Senna starts winding up a basic attack on them. If Senna applies Mist to the same target twice, she collects it, dealing 1% − 16% (based on level) of target's current health as bonus physical damage, and making the target immune to further Mist applications for a few seconds.

description2.value: Enemy units that die near Senna have a chance to spawn a Mist Wraith for 8 seconds, increased to 2 Mist Wraiths for epic monsters. Senna can basic attack a Mist Wraith to destroy it, gaining 3 and collecting its Mist. Enemy champions, large and epic monsters are guaranteed. Minions and lesser monsters that Senna kills have a 4.166% chance. Large minions that Senna doesn't kill are guaranteed, while lesser minions and lesser monsters that Senna doesn't kill have a 22% chance.

description3.value: Innate - Absolution: Each stack of Mist grants Senna  0.75 bonus attack damage. For every 20 stacks, Senna also gains  25 bonus range and  15% critical strike chance. Upon exceeding 100% critical strike chance, Senna converts 35% of the excess into  life steal.

description4.value: Innate - Relic Cannon: Senna's basic attacks deal 20% AD bonus physical damage on-hit and grant 10 / 15 / 20% of the target's movement speed as  bonus movement speed for 0.5 seconds on-hit.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Dodge prevents from marking and collecting a Mist via Senna's basic attacks and Piercing Darkness. PENDING FOR TEST: Mist interaction with block and blind. Nunu & Willump spawn a wraith each. Enemies will not see newly spawned wraiths while Senna is not visible. Minions executed by allies with Spoils of War have a 8.33% chance to spawn wraiths. A wraith can be hit by Cosmic Binding and it will interact with it the same way minions or monsters interact with Cosmic Binding but it will not take damage. Mist Wraith has a spawn animation, but is targetable immediately. Mist Wraith grants a small amount of sight around itself. Runaan's Hurricane secondary bolts will ignore Mist Wraiths. Excluding the range increase, one stack of Mist values approx. 40.5 ( +3 from Mist Wraith pickup). The bonuses have a gross value of 56.25 ( 35.25 with life steal).  0.75 AD is worth 26.25‬. Absolution effectively boosts basic attacks with 0.9 AD, making the value 31.5.  0.75% critical strike chance is worth 30. Absolution reduces its efficiency by 70%, making the value 9.  0.26% life steal is worth ≈ 9.

notes.value: * Piercing Darkness' cast time scales linearily with Senna's champion level and scales non-linearily with her  bonus attack speed (beyond her per-level attack speed). Senna can generally target anything that is not either explicitly untargetable or herself. Valid targets include anything that can be targeted by a basic attack from someone. Piercing Darkness will attempt to lead the target if it is moving but does not adjust further during cast time (enemies can dodge the laser if they change their position by a sufficient amount during the cast time). It leads by (up-to?) 80 units. On-hit effects are applied in order of struck units' spawn IDs. This matters for effects that are consumed on-hit (e.g. Duskblade of Draktharr, Spellblade), which are applied to the target with the lowest Spawn ID. "Spawn ID" is an unofficial abbreviation to describe the spawn order for all units at the beginning of games, below are some examples. If Senna targets an enemy champion but hits at least one more enemy champion simultaneously, Press the Attack's first stack will be applied to that target. If no champion was targeted, it will default to the champion with the lowest Spawn ID out of the ones struck by the ability. Whether the effect stacks up on a champion or not when multiple enemy champions are stuck also depends on Spawn ID. If Piercing Darkness struck an enemy champion and turret simultaneously, with Rapid Firecannon fully charged, the passive effect will most likely proc on the turret since towers are often spawned before champions. Since Piercing Darkness is treated as a basic attack to turrets, its damage is valid for the damage conversion from physical to magic when attacking them. Spell shield will not prevent on-hit effects from being applied. PENDING FOR TEST: Piercing Darkness interaction with dodging, blocking, and blinding effects.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Curse of the Black Mist.

blurb.value: Senna dissolves into a cloud of mist, gaining movement speed and camouflaging her and her nearby allies. Teammates who emerge from the mist appear as unclickable wraiths to enemies until they either attack or get close.

description.value: Active: Senna surrounds herself with an aura of mist and gains camouflage for a duration. If Senna breaks the camouflage, she can regain it until after 1.75 seconds of not performing actions that break stealth.

description2.value: Allied champions who enter the mist gain Wraith Form for a duration equal to the remaining duration.

description3.value: Wraith Form: Gain camouflage. Enemies will have obscured vision of Wraiths moving outside of the mist. Wraith Form can be regained if lost by breaking the camouflage after 1.75 seconds of not performing actions that break stealth. Wraith Form ends immediately upon Senna's death.

description4.value: Senna and allies camouflaged by Curse of the Black Mist also gain  20% bonus movement speed.

notes.value: * Senna can move while casting. Allies affected by the Curse of the Blast Mist aura receive a buff called Cloak of Mist. Obscured units appear as Wraiths, hence the name. The wraith model does not distinguish which champion is obscured. On the mini-map, obscured champions will be displayed as wraith icons instead of champion icons to the enemy team. In-game, the 'Cloak of Mist' buff grants camouflage and the 'Wraith Form' buff obscures the unit and grants movement speed. However, 'Cloak of Mist' has the unspecified effect of negating the obscuring effects of 'Wraith Form' (i.e. the unit is not a wraith while inside the mist); the unit has the bonus movement speed even when they are not a wraith (e.g. inside the mist or an enemy is nearby); and 'Wraith Form' also grants the functionality of camouflage (i.e. the unit is treated as a camouflaged unit with regards to True Sight, Control Wards, and enemy champions). Given this overly complex interaction between the two buffs granted as well as the overlapping effects, it is easier to describe the effects as a single buff that is modified in specific circumstances rather than trying to establish a new game mechanic. Senna likewise has her aura buff and the 'Wraith Form' buff, but her 'Wraith Form' does not share gameplay functionality with other allies benefiting from Wraith Form. For Senna, the appearance of being a wraith is a form-swap while camouflaged (similar to Evelynn's Demon Shade). Senna will remain in her wraith form when she is detected so long as the camouflage effect isn't broken, and her wraith's appearance is very distinct from other wraiths. Oracle's Extract has no effect on champions with the Cloak of Mist buff, even though Oracle's Extract has a range of 500, while the camouflage radius is only 280 or 400 in the case of Senna herself. Wraith Form will not be granted to allies that are in a zombie state or are channeling. It will be granted to allies even if they are untargetable.
